%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Would%20Literally%20Turn%20Criminal%20Law%20on%20its%20Head'%3A%20What%20J%26amp%3BK%20HC%20Said%20While%20Granting%20Fahad%20Shah%20Bail%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F06194949%2Ffahad-shah-.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EPunching%20holes%20in%20the%20police%20chargesheet%2C%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20high%20court%20has%20struck%20down%20the%20terror%20funding%20charge%20against%20Kashmiri%20journalist%20Fahad%20Shah%20while%20linking%20the%20%E2%80%98seditious%E2%80%99%20article%20in%20his%20media%20outlet%20to%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20granted%20bail%20to%20Shah%20on%20November%2017%2C%20nearly%20two%20years%20after%20he%20was%20first%20arrested%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%20on%20terrorism%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHearing%20his%20bail%20application%2C%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20high%20court%20observed%20that%20invoking%20charges%20of%20terrorism%20against%20Shah%20for%20an%2011-year-old%20article%20%E2%80%9Ccollide(s)%20head%20long%20with%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20enshrined%20in%20Article%2019%20of%20the%20Constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98The%20shackles%20of%20slavery%20will%20break%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20controversial%20article%20authored%20by%20Aala%20Fazili%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20scholar%2C%20appeared%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%20outlet%2C%20which%20was%20founded%20by%20Shah%2C%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Aala%20and%20Shah%20were%20arrested%20last%20year%20in%20the%20anti-terror%20case%20which%20was%20filed%20in%20Jammu%20CIJ%20police%20station%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%E2%80%99s%20State%20Investigation%20Agency%20(SIA).%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20bail%20application%20was%20earlier%20rejected%20by%20a%20lower%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SIA%20has%20accused%20the%20two%20of%20glorifying%20terrorism%2C%20terror%20conspiracy%20and%20waging%20war%20against%20the%20country%20besides%20a%20slew%20of%20other%20charges%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%201967%20(UAPA)%20and%20Foreign%20Contributions%20Regulation%20Act%20(FCRA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prosecution%20had%20invoked%20Section%2043-D%20(5)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20to%20oppose%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20bail%20application.%20Under%20this%20section%2C%20a%20court%20cannot%20grant%20bail%20to%20a%20UAPA%20suspect%20without%20hearing%20the%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposing%20the%20bail%20application%2C%20the%20prosecution%20pleaded%20that%20the%20controversial%20article%20in%20The%20Kashmir%20Walla%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98terrorist%20attack%E2%80%99%20defined%20in%20section%2015%20(1)%20(a)%20(ii)%20of%20the%20UAPA.%20The%20prosecution%20claimed%20that%20the%20article%20had%20attacked%20the%20%E2%80%9Chonour%2C%20dignity%20and%20fair%20name%E2%80%9D%20of%20India%20which%20was%20her%20%E2%80%9Cincorporeal%E2%80%9D%20property%20under%20section%202%20(h)%20of%20the%20UAPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArgument%20%E2%80%98would%20literally%20turn%20criminal%20law%20on%20its%20head%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERejecting%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20argument%20that%20the%20anti-terror%20case%20was%20beyond%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20purview%20at%20this%20stage%20as%20charges%20have%20been%20framed%20by%20the%20trial%20court%2C%20the%20HC%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Mohan%20Lal%20and%20Justice%20Atul%20Sreedharan%20observed%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Csuperficial%20analysis%20of%20%E2%80%A6%20evidence%20was%20necessary%E2%80%9D%20to%20decide%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20bail%20application%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20so%20in%20a%20case%20where%20the%20bar%20of%20section%2043-D%20(5)%20is%20raised.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDismissing%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20argument%20that%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20article%20was%20a%20terrorist%20attack%20on%20India%2C%20the%20division%20bench%20observed%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20this%20argument%20is%20accepted%2C%20it%20would%20literally%20turn%20criminal%20law%20on%20its%20head.%20It%20would%20mean%20that%20any%20criticism%20of%20the%20central%20government%20can%20be%20described%20as%20a%20terrorist%20act%20because%20the%20honour%20of%20India%20is%20its%20incorporeal%20property.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20continued%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20legislature%20would%20have%20to%20make%20the%20act%20of%20expressing%2C%20in%20any%20manner%20whatsoever%2C%20a%20disparaging%20thought%20of%20India%2C%20a%20specific%20offence.%20The%20average%20Indian%20in%20the%20street%20who%20must%20suffer%20the%20consequences%20must%20be%20made%20well%20aware%20beforehand%20that%20his%20negative%20opinion%20of%20India%2C%20expressed%20in%20words%20or%20in%20writing%20or%20any%20other%20form%20giving%20permanence%2C%20could%20visit%20him%20with%20severe%20sanction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelving%20into%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20and%20terrorist%20activities%20under%20the%20UAPA%2C%20the%20court%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20prosecution%20has%20not%20provided%20any%20evidence%20of%20violence%20or%20attack%20on%20security%20forces%20due%20to%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20controversial%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Prima%20facie%20at%20fault%20for%20his%20mental%20state%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20a%20news%20report%20in%20The%20Kashmir%20Walla%20which%20had%20mentioned%20the%20last%20phone%20conversation%20of%20a%20militant%20before%20his%20killing%20in%20Shopian%20district%20on%20April%2011%2C%202021%20and%20which%2C%20the%20prosecution%20alleged%2C%20glorified%20violence%2C%20the%20court%20held%20that%20the%20report%C2%A0is%20based%20on%20facts%20which%20%E2%80%9Cneither%20endorses%20the%20sentiments%20of%20the%20militant%20and%20neither%20(%3Cem%3Esic%3C%2Fem%3E)%20does%20it%20glorify%20the%20militant.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20arguments%2C%20the%20prosecution%20also%20told%20the%20court%20that%20some%20unpublished%20poems%20recovered%20during%20searches%20at%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20home%20and%20office%20showed%20his%20%E2%80%9Cseparatist%20mentality%E2%80%9D%20but%20the%20court%20observed%20that%20these%20%E2%80%9Creflect%20his%20fondness%20for%20the%20valley%20and%20freedom%2C%20as%20also%20his%20pain%20and%20anguish%20at%20the%C2%A0turmoil%E2%80%9D%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20prosecution%20wants%20the%20court%20to%20hold%20the%C2%A0appellant%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eprima%20facie%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Eat%20fault%20for%20his%20mental%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20pointed%20out%20dryly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20chargesheet%20filed%20last%20year%2C%20the%20SIA%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20elite%20counterterrorism%20agency%20which%20was%20formed%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20had%20also%20sought%20to%20link%20the%20recent%20protests%20and%20militancy-related%20incidents%20in%20Kashmir%20to%20the%20article%20which%2C%20the%20agency%20said%2C%20also%20led%20to%20the%20radicalisation%20of%20Kashmiri%20youngsters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20framed%20charges%20against%20Shah%20in%20March%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20charge%20sheet%2C%20the%20article%20was%20allegedly%20part%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecessionist-cum%20terrorist%20campaign%E2%80%9D%20to%20incite%20the%20youth%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20into%20adopting%20%E2%80%9Cviolent%20means%20of%20protest%20to%20secede%20from%20India%20and%20accede%20to%20Pakistan.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20senior%20advocate%20and%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20P.N.%20Raina%2C%20informed%20the%20bench%20that%20none%20of%20the%2044%20witnesses%20listed%20in%20the%20charge%20sheet%20or%20documents%20collected%20as%20evidence%20during%20the%20course%20of%20investigation%20by%20the%20SIA%20suggest%20that%20the%20article%20had%20influenced%20people%20to%20take%20up%20arms%20or%20resort%20to%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Stretching%20causation%20to%20absurd%20limits%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20ruled%20that%20there%20was%20no%20reference%20to%20the%20accession%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20with%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20article%20nor%20any%20call%20to%20arms%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20incitement%20to%20violence%20of%20any%20kind%20much%20less%20acts%20of%20terrorism%20or%20of%20undermining%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20State%20with%20acts%20of%20violence%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20cannot%20be%20presumed%20reasonably%20that%20the%20instances%20of%20stone%20pelting%20that%20may%20have%20taken%20place%20in%202022%20were%20on%20account%20of%20the%20instigation%20of%20the%20offending%20article%20that%20was%20uploaded%20in%20the%20year%202011.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvoking%20the%20Latin%20maxim%20%E2%80%98%3Ci%3Ecausa%20proxima%20non%20remota%20jura%20spectator%3C%2Fi%3Eor%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20court%20observed%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cproximate%20cause%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20article%20was%20important%20to%20fix%20liability.%20%E2%80%9CAffixing%20liability%C2%A0for%20the%20offences%20between%202020%20to%202022%20based%20on%20the%20article%20written%20and%20published%20in%202011%20would%20be%20stretching%20causation%20to%20absurd%C2%A0limits%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20SIA%20chargesheet%2C%20Shah%20has%20received%20funding%20of%20Rs%2095%20lakh%20for%20%E2%80%98The%20Kashmir%20Walla%E2%80%99%20since%20its%20inception%20which%2C%20the%20agency%20said%2C%20could%20have%20been%20allegedly%20used%20for%20terror%20activities.%20However%2C%20the%20HC%20observed%20that%20the%20trial%20court%20has%20framed%20charges%20of%20FCRA%20violation%20against%20Shah%20and%20not%20section%2017%20of%20the%20UAPA%20which%20deals%20with%20punishment%20for%20terror%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20apprehension%20sounded%20by%20the%20State%20that%20the%20funds%20received%20by%20the%20Appellant%20which%20includes%20overseas%20remittances%20could%20have%20been%20used%20for%20terror%C2%A0funding%20is%20summarily%20rejected%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20ruled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwo%20questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%20of%20the%20bail%20order%2C%20the%20division%20bench%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20was%20mulling%20over%20two%20questions%3B%20one%2C%20whether%20section%2043-D%20(5)%20of%20the%20UAP%20Act%20where%2C%20despite%20the%20existence%20of%20a%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eprima%20facie%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Ecase%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98Need%20to%20Arrest%E2%80%99%20would%20violate%20the%20right%20to%20life%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D%20and%2C%20the%20court%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9Cif%20it%20does%2C%20whether%20the%20Court%20can%20still%20grant%20bail%20on%20account%20of%20the%20violation%20of%20Article%2021%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20added%20on%20the%20second%20question%3A%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20whether%2C%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%98Clear%20and%20Present%20Danger%E2%80%99%20ought%20to%20be%20taken%20into%20account%20by%20the%20Courts%20while%20deciding%20a%20bail%20application%20where%20the%20bar%20under%20section%2043-D%20(5)%20is%20applicable%3F%E2%80%9D%20In%20this%20instance%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20prosecution%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20prove%20the%20charge%20of%20%E2%80%98clear%20and%20present%20danger%E2%80%99%20against%20Shah%20while%20granting%20him%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20quashed%20the%20charges%20under%20Sections%2018%20(terror%20conspiracy)%20and%20121%20(waging%20war%20against%20the%20country)%20of%20the%20UAP%20Act%20and%20153-B%20(imputations%2C%20assertions%20prejudicial%20to%20national-integration)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20against%20Shah%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20his%20release%20from%20jail%20where%20he%20has%20been%20held%20for%20nearly%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20(Shah)%20will%20face%20trial%20under%20Section%2013%20(abetting%20unlawful%20activities)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20and%20Sections%2035%20(receiving%20foreign%20funds%20illegally)%20and%2039%20(offences%20by%20companies)%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raina%2C%20his%20counsel%2C%20told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700544327000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F06194949%2Ffahad-shah-.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffahad-shah-jammu-kashmir-high-court-order%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'It%20would%20mean%20that%20any%20criticism%20of%20the%20central%20government%20can%20be%20described%20as%20a%20terrorist%20act%20because%20the%20honour%20of%20India%20is%20its%20incorporeal%20property.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffahad-shah-jammu-kashmir-high-court-order%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Union%20to%20SC%3A%20%E2%80%9828%20States%2FUTs%20Appoint%20Nodal%20Officers%20to%20Tackle%20Hate%20Speech%20Under%202018%20Guidelines%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20has%20informed%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%2028%20states%20have%20appointed%20nodal%20officers%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20guidelines%20issued%20by%20the%20court%20during%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ETehseen%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EPoonawalla%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20case%20to%20prevent%20mob%20violence%20and%20lynching%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20status%20report%20was%20filed%20by%20the%20Union%20in%20response%20to%20a%20batch%20of%20petitions%20seeking%20directions%20to%20curb%20hate%20speech%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2F28-states-have-appointed-nodal-officers-in-terms-of-directions-in-tehseen-poonawalla-judgment-centre-tells-supreme-court-242621%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2025%2C%20while%20hearing%20these%20petitions%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20had%20asked%20the%20home%20ministry%20to%20collate%20information%20from%20states%20regarding%20the%20appointment%20of%20nodal%20officers%20and%20file%20a%20status%20report%20within%20three%20weeks.%20It%20had%20also%20said%20that%20if%20any%20state%20government%20does%20not%20furnish%20said%20details%2C%20then%20the%20top%20court%20should%20be%20apprised%20of%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20recommended%20the%20Parliament%20create%20a%20special%20law%20against%20lynching%2C%20emphasising%20that%20%E2%80%9Cfear%20of%20law%20and%20veneration%20for%20the%20command%20of%20law%20constitute%20the%20foundation%20of%20a%20civilised%20society%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20had%20also%20issued%20a%20series%20of%20directions%20to%20prevent%20mob%20lynching%2C%20including%20the%20mandate%20for%20appointing%20nodal%20officers%20in%20every%20district%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwatch-why-doesnt-the-government-have-separate-mob-lynching-data%5C%22%3EWhy%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20the%20Government%20Have%20Separate%20Mob%20Lynching%20Data%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20had%20pulled%20up%20the%20Union%20and%2010%20state%20governments%20in%202019%20for%20not%20implementing%20the%20directions%20issued%20by%20it%20to%20curb%20mob%20lynching%20and%20violence%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3E