xasattorneygeneral.gov%2Fnews%2Freleases%2Fattorney-general-ken-paxton-opens-investigation-media-matters-potential-fraudulent-activity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaying%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20troubled%26quot%3B%20by%20Musk's%20allegations.%20His%20statement%20called%20Media%20Matters%20a%20%26quot%3Bradical%20anti-free%20speech%20organization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20examining%20the%20issue%20closely%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20public%20has%20not%20been%20deceived%20by%20the%20schemes%20of%20radical%20left-wing%20organizations%20who%20would%20like%20nothing%20more%20than%20to%20limit%20freedom%20by%20reducing%20participation%20in%20the%20public%20square%2C%26quot%3B%20Paxton%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Musk's%20part%2C%20the%20billionaire's%20X%20Corp%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20in%20Texas%20alleging%20that%20Media%20Matters%20launched%20a%20%26quot%3Bblatant%20smear%20campaign%26quot%3B%20against%20the%20social%20media%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20accuses%20Media%20Matters%20of%20%26quot%3Bendlessly%20scrolling%20and%20refreshing%20its%20unrepresentative%2C%20hand-selected%20feed%26quot%3B%20to%20generate%20its%20report%2C%20which%20was%20released%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20watchdog's%20analysis%20had%20shown%20examples%20of%20ads%20from%20five%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20IBM%2C%20Oracle%2C%20Xfinity%2C%20Bravo%2C%20and%20Apple%20%E2%80%94%20next%20to%20antisemitic%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20X's%20lawsuit%20alleges%20that%20no%20%26quot%3Bauthentic%26quot%3B%20users%20on%20X%20saw%20the%20combination%20of%20ads%20and%20pro-Nazi%20content%20that%20Media%20Matters%20found%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20one%20other%20user%20who%20saw%20Apple's%20ad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20calls%20for%20Media%20Matters%20to%20take%20down%20its%20report%20and%20asks%20for%20an%20undisclosed%20amount%20in