090%25%20of%20Bhutanese%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bmf.bt%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2FSocial-Media-Landscape-in-Bhutan.pdf%5C%22%3Eusing%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20social%20media%20penetrating%20all%20remote%20areas%20in%20Bhutan%2C%20Dechen%E2%80%99s%20relatives%20in%20remote%20villages%20are%20connected%20on%20WeChat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20in%20three%20WeChat%20groups%20where%20people%20usually%20communicate%20through%20voice%20messages%20in%20their%20native%20language.%20Most%20WeChat%20users%20in%20rural%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20communicate%20in%20their%20oral%20native%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20learn%20many%20words.%20I%20learnt%20how%20to%20say%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20in%20my%20own%20language%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20mother%20of%20two%20now%20living%20in%20Western%20Australia%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDechen%E2%80%99s%20story%20is%20not%20isolated.%20Social%20media%20is%20giving%20a%20new%20lifeline%20to%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20native%20languages%2C%20which%20do%20not%20have%20written%20script%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dzongkha.gov.bt%2Fuploads%2Ffiles%2Farticles%2FA_Paper_on_Language_Policy_%26amp%3B_Planning_in_Bhutan_by_Pema_Wangdi_c8e8caeee831129a3be15aa6e99732c2.pdf%5C%22%3Elack%20proper%20documentation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%20communicating%20through%20voice%20messages%2C%20social%20media%20is%20giving%20Bhutanese%20people%20in%20both%20urban%20and%20rural%20areas%20a%20new%20opportunity%20to%20use%20their%20local%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELosing%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20languages%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhutan%20is%20a%20tiny%20Himalayan%20nation%20with%20a%20population%20of%20under%20800%2C000%20people.%20Internet%20and%20television%20was%20introduced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffid4sa-repository.ub.uni-heidelberg.de%2F2656%2F1%2FBhutanese_Media.pdf%5C%22%3Eonly%20in%201999%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20mobile%20phones%20in%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20has%20more%20than%2020%20local%20languages%2C%20but%20only%20Dzongkha%20has%20written%20text%20and%20is%20promoted%20as%20the%20national%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20struggles%20to%20promote%20the%20national%20language%20and%20its%20usage%20against%20English.%20Today%20most%20urban%20residents%2C%20especially%20the%20elites%2C%20speak%20English%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffactsanddetails.com%2Fsouth-asia%2FBhutan%2FPeople_Bhutan%2Fentry-7897.html%5C%22%3Etheir%20primary%20language%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20languages%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20minority%20languages%20%E2%80%93%20are%20vanishing%20or%20becoming%20endangered%20as%20younger%20generations%20switch%20to%20Dzongkha%20and%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20medium%20of%20instruction%20in%20schools%20is%20mostly%20in%20English%3B%20Dzongkha%20is%20taught%20only%20as%20grammar%20and%20literature.%20Students%20are%20shamed%20and%20often%20punished%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Flanguage-policy-decolonising-the-mind%2F%5C%22%3Eusing%20their%20local%20languages%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20preservation%20and%20promotion%20of%20local%20languages%2C%20therefore%2C%20depends%20on%20the%20speakers.%20A%20language%20faces%20extinction%20when%20its%20speakers%20die%20out%20or%20switch%20to%20another%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELinguist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fuser%3DPrIZwrkAAAAJ%26hl%3Den%5C%22%3EPema%20Wangdi%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20researched%20languages%20in%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20he%20told%20me%20many%20people%20are%20losing%20their%20native%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20lose%20our%20language%2C%20we%20lose%20a%20piece%20of%20our%20national%20identity%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWangdi%20has%20identified%20there%20are%20no%20longer%20any%20speakers%20of%20Olekha%2C%20an%20indigenous%20dialect%20of%20Rukha%20in%20Wangdu%20Phodrang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20loss%20of%20a%20single%20language%20is%20a%20loss%20of%20a%20piece%20of%20our%20national%20linguistic%20heritage%20and%20identity%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20a%20language%20is%20lost%2C%20cultural%20traditions%20which%20are%20tied%20to%20that%20language%20such%20as%20songs%2C%20myths%20and%20poetry%20will%20be%20lost%20forever.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20Bhutanese%20languages%20%E2%80%93%20including%20Tshophu%20language%20of%20Doyaps%20in%20Samtse%2C%20Monpa%20language%20of%20central%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20Gongdukha%20of%20Mongar%20%E2%80%93%20are%20endangered%20and%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dzongkha.gov.bt%2Fuploads%2Ffiles%2Farticles%2FA_Paper_on_Language_Policy_%26amp%3B_Planning_in_Bhutan_by_Pema_Wangdi_c8e8caeee831129a3be15aa6e99732c2.pdf%5C%22%3Ebrink%20of%20extinction%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPreservation%20of%20local%20languages%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20future%20of%20minority%20languages%20is%20under%20threat.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FConstitution_of_Bhutan%5C%22%3EThe%20Constitution%20of%20Bhutan%3C%2Fa%3E%20mandates%20the%20preservation%20and%20promotion%20of%20local%20languages%2C%20but%20there%20are%20no%20official%20efforts%20to%20preserve%20native%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20encouraging%20people%20to%20speak%20their%20native%20languages%20can%20have%20far-reaching%20benefits%20in%20preserving%20and%20promoting%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20rich%20culture%20and%20tradition.%20Language%20embodies%20identity%2C%20ethnicity%20and%20cultural%20values%3A%20a%20thriving%20local%20language%20would%20help%20transfer%20this%20intangible%20wealth%20to%20the%20younger%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20could%20be%20an%20invaluable%20tool%20in%20this%20preservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhutan%20could%20save%20its%20languages%20from%20becoming%20extinct%20with%20promotion%20of%20social%20media%20usage%20and%20language%20education%20could%20be%20done%20on%20social%20media%20platforms.%20With%20both%20young%20and%20old%20people%20glued%20to%20social%20media%2C%20encouraging%20more%20people%20to%20use%20local%20languages%20in%20social%20media%20could%20generate%20interest%20among%20the%20youth%20to%20learn%20their%20local%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20also%20help%20in%20documenting%20the%20endangered%20local%20languages%20as%20the%20older%20generation%20can%20record%20their%20voices%20on%20WeChat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20elder%20citizens%20feel%20strongly%20about%20their%20language%20and%20emphasise%20teaching%20their%20mother%20tongue%20to%20the%20younger%20generation%20and%20their%20grandchildren.%20Social%20media%20%E2%80%93%20joining%20the%20younger%20generation%20on%20platforms%20where%20they%20feel%20at%20home%20%E2%80%93%20could%20be%20the%20way%20forward.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F210280%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETashi%20Dema%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20PhD%20candidate%20in%20language%20and%20politics%2C%20University%20of%20New%20England.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhow-social-media-is-breathing-new-life-into-bhutans-unwritten-local-languages-210280%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700535626000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20182217%2Fpema-gyamtsho-dtwwEJcr8R8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fsocial-media-breathing-new-life-bhutan-unwritten-local-languages%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22By%20communicating%20through%20voice%20messages%2C%20social%20media%20is%20giving%20Bhutanese%20people%20in%20both%20urban%20and%20rural%20areas%20a%20new%20opportunity%20to%20use%20their%20local%20language.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fsocial-media-breathing-new-life-bhutan-unwritten-local-languages%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Satya%20Nadella%20says%20he%20wants%20governance%20changes%20on%20OpenAI's%20board%20but%20didn't%20say%20if%20Microsoft%20is%20getting%20a%20seat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%20and%20Satya%20Nadella%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e043136d588dc55ce4424%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221741%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20and%20OpenAI%20CEOs%20Satya%20Nadella%20and%20Sam%20Altman%20at%20OpenAI's%20first%20developer%20conference.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20said%20that%20he%20wants%20changes%20to%20the%20OpenAI%20board%20after%20it%20fired%20Sam%20Altman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENadella%20did%20not%20specify%20what%20changes%20he%20would%20want%20made.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENadella%20was%20blindsided%20by%20the%20abrupt%20firing%20of%20Altman%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20whirlwind%20weekend%20of%20departures%20and%20internal%20protests%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20the%20company's%20most%20significant%20investor%20and%20partner%20wants%20a%20change%20to%20the%20board%20that%20started%20the%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo-satya-nadella-sam-altman-openai-ousted-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20on%20a%20media%20blitz%20Monday%20afternoon%20speaking%20to%20CNBC%2C%20BloombergTV%2C%20and%20Kara%20Swisher.%20During%20these%20interviews%2C%20he%20offered%20nothing%20but%20praise%20for%20recently%20ousted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ousted-fired-openai-ceo-chatgpt-maker-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebut%20made%20comments%20about%20OpenAI's%20board%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FCNBC%2Fstatus%2F1726744999281254740%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECNBC%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20has%20to%20change%26quot%3B%20in%20regards%20to%20the%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20but%20stopped%20short%20of%20saying%20what%20changes%20he%20would%20like%20to%20see%20%E2%80%94%20including%20whether%20or%20not%20Microsoft%20should%20have%20its%20own%20seat%20at%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20at%20this%20point%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20very%2C%20very%20clear%20that%20something%20has%20to%20change%20around%20the%20governance%2C%20and%20we'll%20have%20a%20good%20dialogue%20with%20their%20board%20on%20that%20and%20we'll%20walk%20through%20that%20as%20time%20evolves%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20CNBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20reiterated%20his%20point%20in%20a%20later%20interview%20with%20BloombergTV%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bsurprises%20are%20bad%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20they%20hoped%20to%20prevent%20them%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20things%20are%20done%20in%20a%20way%20that%20will%20allow%20us%20to%20continue%20to%20partner%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20the%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20about%20it.%20This%20idea%20that%20somehow%2C%20sudden%20changes%20happen%20without%20being%20in%20the%20loop%20is%20not%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20tech%20journalist%20Kara%20Swisher%2C%20on%20her%20podcast%20%26quot%3BOn%20With%20Kara%20Swisher%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20hinted%20that%20a%20board%20seat%20or%20observer%20for%20Microsoft%20at%20OpenAI%20was%20a%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20sort%20of%20cross%20that%20if%20it%20happens%2C%20but%20I%20think%20that%20we%20will%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20our%20interests%20are%20solid%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20Swisher%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20about%20a%20board%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20also%20said%20that%20he%20did%20not%20have%20an%20opinion%20on%20whether%20the%20current%20board%20should%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20told%20Swisher%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20he%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo-satya-nadella-sam-altman-openai-ousted-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblindsided%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Friday%20ousting%20of%20Altman%20by%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%20The%20board%20said%20that%20Altman%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20consistently%20candid%20in%20his%20communications%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20lacked%20%26quot%3Bconfidence%26quot%3B%20in%20Altman's%20ability%20to%20lead%20the%20company.%20The%20company%20did%20not%20go%20into%20further%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20told%20Bloomberg%20TV%20that%20he%20is%20still%20unaware%20of%20why%20exactly%20the%20board%20dumped%20Altman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20not%20been%20told%20about%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20Bloomberg%20TV%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BThey%20published%20internally%20at%20OpenAI%20that%20the%20board%20has%20not%20talked%20about%20anything%20that%20Sam%20did%20other%20than%20some%20breakdown%20in%20communications.%20I%20not%20directly%20was%20told%20by%20anyone%20from%20their%20board%20about%20any%20issues%2C%20and%20so%20therefore%20I%20remain%20confident%20in%20Sam%20and%20his%20leadership%20and%20capability.%26quot