5Etfw%5C%22%3EApril%209%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EThe%20official%20said%20that%20the%20Jharkhand%20state%20government%2C%20which%20looks%20after%20the%20health%20and%20nutrition%20needs%20of%20some%20of%20the%20poorest%20communities%20of%20India%2C%20was%20provided%20no%20choice%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20implementing%20this%20new%20policy%2C%20even%20when%20Jharkhand%20lacks%20adequate%20infrastructure%2C%20such%20as%20laboratories%20which%20can%20test%20the%20added%20micronutrient%20content%2C%20to%20ensure%20quality%20control%20and%20safety.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20situation%20came%20to%20this%3A%20the%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%2C%20which%20supplies%20us%20the%20rice%20which%20we%20distribute%20to%20the%20poor%2C%20said%20that%20if%20you%20do%20not%20take%20chemically%20fortified%20rice%2C%20you%20will%20not%20get%20any%20rice.%20Then%20the%20public%20grain%20distribution%20in%20Jharkhand%20would%20stop%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20official.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Jharkhand%2C%20so%20far%2C%20the%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(FCI)%2C%20under%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Consumer%20Affairs%2C%20Food%20and%20Public%20Distribution%2C%20acted%20as%20an%20aggregator.%20Under%20the%20National%20Food%20Security%20Act%2C%20it%20procured%20paddy%20and%20provided%20it%20to%20Jharkhand%20from%20a%20central%20pool.%20After%20the%20paddy%20is%20milled%2C%20it%20is%20transported%20to%20FCI%20warehouses%2C%20and%20then%20the%20state-level%20bodies%20distribute%20it%20further%20at%20retail%20outlets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20food%20ministry%20told%20us%3A%20%E2%80%98If%20you%20wish%20to%20distribute%20simple%20%E2%80%9Ccustom%20made%20rice%E2%80%9D%20(CMR)%20like%20before%2C%20then%20make%20your%20own%20arrangements%20for%20that.%E2%80%99%20The%20Jharkhand%20state%20government%20does%20not%20have%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20do%20so%2C%20without%20FCI%E2%80%99s%20support%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20stated.%20%E2%80%9CState%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eko%20unhone%20majboor%20kiya%20ki%20aap%20ko%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Efortified%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20lena%20hi%20hai%2C%20doosra%20koi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eoption%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20nahi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20(They%20made%20it%20compulsory%20for%20us%2C%20giving%20us%20no%20option%20but%20to%20distribute%20fortified%20food.)%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Mandatory%E2%80%99%20scheme%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20selected%20a%20district%20each%20in%2015%20states%20to%20distribute%20fortified%20rice%20as%20a%20pilot%20scheme.%20It%20started%20distributing%20fortified%20rice%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20food%20safety%20programmes%20in%202022.%20It%20plans%20to%20expand%20this%20scheme%20to%20all%20districts%20of%20India%20by%20March%202024%20with%20a%20yearly%20budget%20of%20nearly%20Rs%203%2C000%20crore%2C%20or%20%24350%20million%20approximately.%20From%20March%202022%2C%20it%20made%20fortified%20rice%20compulsory%20in%20the%20children%E2%80%99s%20schemes.%20From%20March%202023%20onwards%2C%20it%20introduced%20it%20in%20ration%2C%20or%20the%20public%20distribution%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20ration%20scheme%20is%20the%20largest%20food%20safety%20scheme%20in%20the%20world%2C%20reaching%2080%20crore%20or%20800%20million%20individuals.%20For%20a%20comparison%2C%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme(WFP)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wfp.org%2Fstories%2Fwfp-glance%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEach%2520month%2520WFP%2520supports%2520around%2Cwith%2520food%252C%2520cash%2520or%2520vouchers%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereached%20160%20million%20people%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202022.%20After%20years%20of%20advocacy%20by%20grassroots%20activists%E2%80%99%20networks%20such%20as%20the%20Right%20to%20Food%20Campaign%2C%20the%20previous%20government%20expanded%20food%20security%20schemes%20to%20include%2067%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population.%20Under%20the%20National%20Food%20Security%20Act%2C%202013%2C%20every%20member%20of%20a%20poor%20household%20receives%20five%20kg%20of%20grains%2C%20wheat%20or%20rice%2C%20at%20very%20low%20costs%20at%20village%20ration%20shops.%20The%20poorest%20households%20get%2035%20kg%20grains%20each%20month.%20Under%20the%20midday%20meal%20programme%2C%20115%20million%20school%20children%20get%20a%20hot%20cooked%20meal%20daily%2C%20and%20under%20the%20Integrated%20Child%20Development%20Scheme(ICDS)%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20early%20childcare%20program%2C%20158%20million%20infants%2C%20pregnant%20and%20lactating%20women%2C%20get%20supplementary%20nutrition%20at%20community%20creches.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20ICDS%20and%20school%20lunch%20schemes%2C%20the%20government%20supplies%20around%203.5%20million(35%20lakh)%20metric%20tonnes%20of%20iron-fortified%20rice.%20This%20increases%20ten-fold%20to%20more%20than%2035%20million%20(350%20lakh)%20metric%20tonnes%20fortified%20rice%20in%20the%20public%20distribution%20scheme%2C%20when%20scaled%20to%20all%20districts%20by%202024.%20In%20October%20this%20year%2C%20the%20government%20distributed%20nearly%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fannavitran.nic.in%2FFR%2FavFortifiedRice%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E17%2C74%2C153%20metric%20tonnes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20fortified%20rice%20in%20its%20welfare%20schemes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20has%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgh.bmj.com%2Fcontent%2F6%2F2%2Fe004322%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esecond%20highest%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20sickle%20cell%20disease%20burden%20incidence%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20children%20with%20thalassemia-major%20in%20the%20world.%20The%20government%20has%20provided%20a%20few%20numbers%20in%20parliament.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20August%209%2C%202021%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fgovernance%2Fas-told-to-parliament-august-9-2021-no-data-on-sickle-cell-disease-among-tribals-78365%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eresponding%20to%20a%20parliament%20question%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20tribal%20affairs%20Renuka%20Singh%20Saruta%20replied%20that%201%2C13%2C83%2C664%20(1.13%20crore%20or%2011.3%20million)%20persons%20in%20India%20were%20screened%20for%20sickle%20cell%20disease%20and%20%E2%80%9C8.75%25%20(9%2C96%2C368%2C%20or%209%20million)%20tested%20positive%20(trait%20in%20949057%2C%20disease%2047%2C311).%E2%80%9D%20Further%2C%20the%20minister%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cstudies%20undertaken%20by%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research%20show%20prevalence%20of%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia%20across%20the%20country%20is%205-34%25%20(as%20per%20document%20on%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia%20control%20programme%20published%20by%20Government%20of%20Gujarat)%E2%80%9D.%20On%20a%20question%20about%20thalassemia%2C%20on%20March%2020%2C%202020%2C%20the%20government%20replied%20that%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Can%20estimated%2010%2C000-12%2C000%20children%20with%20B%20(the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hopkinsmedicine.org%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-and-diseases%2Fbeta-thalassemia%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeta)-Thalassemia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20are%20born%20every%20year%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20pilots%20conducted%20for%20launching%20the%20intervention%2C%20the%20government%20tested%20how%20the%20supply%20chain%20of%20fortified%20rice%20works%20%E2%80%93%20or%20how%20it%20would%20reach%20from%20the%20manufacturing%20unit%20to%20a%20rice%20mill%2C%20to%20government%20godowns%20to%20retail%20rations%20shops.%20It%20did%20not%20study%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20intervention%20on%20public%20health%2C%20or%20on%20anaemia%2C%20or%20how%20the%20individuals%20with%20certain%20health%20conditions%20would%20tolerate%20this%20rice.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EActivists%20pointed%20out%20that%20despite%20significant%20populations%20being%20at%20risk%2C%20the%20government%20launched%20the%20scheme%20without%20safeguarding%20how%20individuals%20with%20such%20blood%20disorders%20would%20be%20affected%20when%20they%20ate%20the%20fortified%20food%2C%20or%20how%20their%20bodies%20would%20react%20to%20the%20additional%20synthetic%20iron%20in%20food.%20Not%20only%20activists%2C%20but%20even%20members%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20panels%20have%20publicly%20spoken%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS000291652200452X%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eagainst%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20giving%20such%20rice%20to%20those%20suffering%20from%20sickle%20cell%20disease%20and%20thalassemia%20patients.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20iron-fortified%20food%20should%20also%20not%20be%20given%20to%20those%20with%20other%20conditions%20such%20as%20severe%20malnutrition%2C%20and%20newly%20diagnosed%20tuberculosis%2C%20said%20Dr%20Sylvia%20Karpagam%2C%20a%20doctor%20and%20public%20health%20researcher%2C%20who%20works%20on%20right%20to%20health%20and%20nutrition%20among%20marginalised%20communities.%20%E2%80%9CMalnutrition%20and%20tuberculosis%20can%20often%20remain%20undiagnosed%20and%20untreated%20in%20India.%20Then%2C%20why%20are%20policymakers%20surging%20ahead%20with%20iron%20fortification%20of%20rice%20on%20such%20a%20large%20and%20irreversible%20scale%3F%E2%80%9D%20asked%20Dr%20Karpagam.%20%E2%80%9CIs%20it%20because%20these%20conditions%20affect%20the%20poor%20more%20than%20the%20elite%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21070338%2F5.-health-advisory-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21070338%2F5.-health-advisory-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21070338%2F5.-health-advisory-1-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21070338%2F5.-health-advisory-1-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685621%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEach%20gunny%20bag%20of%20fortified%20rice%20in%20the%20ration%20system%20carries%20a%20health%20warning%20in%20small%20print%20in%20English%2C%20a%20language%20neither%20understood%20nor%20spoken%20by%20the%20majority%20of%20poor.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBalram%2C%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Food%20Campaign%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20to%20study%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20fortified%20rice%20scheme%20in%20Jharkhand%20and%20Chhattisgarh.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20tracked%20it%20in%20four%20villages%20in%20two%20pilot%20blocks.%20Printing%20a%20health%20warning%20in%20small%20print%20in%20English%20in%20rural%20areas%20is%20totally%20ineffective.%20And%20anyway%2C%20the%20rice%20is%20distributed%20to%20the%20poor%20as%20loose%20grains%2C%20not%20in%20bags%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CDespite%20the%20formal%20warning%2C%20we%20found%20grassroots%20health%20workers%20had%20no%20instructions%20to%20make%20this%20distinction%20for%20the%20affected%20individuals%20in%20the%20villages.%20It%20shows%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20utter%20lack%20of%20concern.%20There%20are%20no%20real%20safeguards%20to%20enforce%20it.%20Yet%2C%20the%20scheme%20has%20been%20scaled%20up%2C%20like%20a%20royal%20diktat%20disregarding%20the%20palate%2C%20food%20habits%2C%20taste%20of%20millions.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EActivist%20Rajesh%20Krishnan%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20campaign%2C%20filed%20a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20last%20December%20over%20the%20impact%20on%20health%20of%20such%20vulnerable%20groups.%20Hearing%20the%20case%20last%20month%2C%20the%20court%20asked%20the%20government%20to%20respond%20in%20November.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20the%20evidence%20the%20Union%20government%20considered%20in%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20favour%20was%20a%20randomised%20control%20trial%20(a%20study%20in%20which%20two%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20one%20which%20receives%20an%20intervention%20and%20the%20other%20which%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%93%20are%20compared)%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20fortified%20rice%20on%20reducing%20anaemia%20conducted%20by%20the%20Tata%20Trusts%2C%20which%20is%20a%20philanthropic%20initiative%20of%20the%20Indian%20multinational%20Tata%20Sons.%20The%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%20(BMGF)%20has%20funded%20Tata%20Trusts%20to%20advocate%20for%20and%20work%20on%20fortification%20in%20India.%20For%20instance%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gatesfoundation.org%2Fabout%2Fcommitted-grants%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20gave%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3ESir%20Dorabji%20Tata%20Trusts%20US%20%24%203%20million%20for%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CFood%20Fortification%20MIYCN%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ematernal%20and%20child%20nutrition)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Joint%20Programming%20Platform%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%202016.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFood%20and%20health%20activists%20have%20criticised%20relying%20on%20such%20sources%20which%20were%20conducting%20%E2%80%9Cfriendly%20research%E2%80%9D%20financed%20by%20lobbying%20groups%20as%20a%20potential%20conflict%20of%20interest.%20Tata%20is%20a%20conglomerate%20which%20owns%20several%20businesses%2C%20including%20in%20chemicals%2C%20food%20and%20in%20nutraceutical%20sectors.%20Moreover%2C%20even%20this%20promotional%20study%20conducted%20by%20Tata%20Trusts%20in%20Gadchiroli%20district%2C%20one%20of%20the%20poorest%20parts%20of%20Maharashtra%20in%20western%20India%2C%20which%20is%20a%20glowing%20evaluation%20of%20such%20an%20intervention%2C%20was%20cautious%20on%20providing%20the%20rice%20to%20those%20with%20sickle%20cell%20disease.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortification.fssai.gov.in%2Fassets%2Fevent%2Ffile%2Fimpact-assesment-of-rice-fortification-dr-dk.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETata%20Trusts%20study%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20recorded%20a%20%E2%80%9Closs%20of%20sample%E2%80%9D.%20It%20had%20to%20exclude%20a%20sizeable%20number%20of%20individuals%20from%20the%20study%20sample%20because%20it%20found%20they%20%E2%80%9Csuffered%20from%20sickle%20cell%20disease%E2%80%9D.%20Ministries%E2%80%99%20correspondence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reporters-collective.in%2Fprojects%2Fmodified-rice-papers%5C%22%3Efirst%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Reporters%E2%80%99%20Collective%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20notes%20that%20in%20blood%20tests%2C%20%E2%80%9C7.4%25%20mothers%20at%20Kurkheda%2C%2017.1%25%20at%20Bhamragarh%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9C15%25%20adolescent%20girls%20at%20Kurkheda%2C%2010.3%25%20at%20Bhamragarh%E2%80%9D%20and%20among%20children%2C%20%E2%80%9C9.5%25%20at%20Kurkheda%2C%208.2%25%20at%20Bhamragarh%E2%80%9D%20were%20found%20to%20%E2%80%9Chave%20sickle%20cell%20disease%E2%80%9D.%20The%20evaluators%20avoided%20feeding%20iron-fortified%20rice%20to%20these%20women%2C%20adolescents%20and%20children%20who%20suffered%20from%20the%20blood%20disorder%20resulting%20from%20a%20flawed%20haemoglobin%20mechanism%20in%20their%20bodies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21070810%2F5.2-Tata-Trusts-Study-recorded-loss-of-sample-from-sickle-cell-anemia.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22884%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21070810%2F5.2-Tata-Trusts-Study-recorded-loss-of-sample-from-sickle-cell-anemia.png%20884w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21070810%2F5.2-Tata-Trusts-Study-recorded-loss-of-sample-from-sickle-cell-anemia-300x66.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685622%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22195%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Tata%20Trusts%20study%20recorded%20that%20they%20could%20not%20study%20those%20with%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20had%20ignored%20that%20even%20such%20studies%2C%20financed%20by%20entities%20such%20as%20Tata%2C%20had%20avoided%20giving%20this%20rice%20to%20vulnerable%20groups.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20all%20studies%2C%20certain%20groups%20are%20excluded%20and%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20fully%20know%20or%20understand%20the%20impact%20on%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20explained%20a%20doctor%20working%20in%20the%20government%2C%20who%20declined%20to%20be%20named.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20no%20way%20to%20know%20the%20full%20impact%20on%20such%20groups.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMedical%20experts%20explained%20one%20of%20the%20less%20understood%20concerns%2C%20firstly%2C%20how%20excess%20iron%20may%20get%20stored%20in%20a%20form%20that%20was%20of%20no%20use%20to%20the%20body%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20it%20could%20do%20harm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CStudies%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0002916523233171%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshow%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20some%20such%20patients%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20down-regulate%20their%20iron%20absorption%2C%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20absorb%20iron.%20The%20problem%20with%20excess%20iron%20is%20that%20it%20ends%20up%20in%20a%20toxic%20form%20in%20the%20blood%2C%E2%80%9D%20explained%20Dr%20Anura%20Kurpad%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20St%20John%E2%80%99s%20Medical%20College%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20who%20chaired%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research%E2%80%99s%20(ICMR)%20expert%20committee%20on%20nutrient%20requirements%2C%20and%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20scientific%20committee%20of%20the%20food%20regulatory%20body%2C%20the%20Food%20Safety%20and%20Standards%20Authority%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CThis%20excess%20iron%20that%20is%20unbound%20to%20the%20usual%20transport%20protein%20called%20transferrin%20is%20(quite%20unimaginatively)%20called%20%E2%80%9Cnon%20transferrin%20bound%20iron%E2%80%9D%20or%20NTBI.%20This%20is%20particularly%20toxic%20as%20it%20forms%20reactive%20oxidative%20species%20that%20cause%20a%20lot%20of%20damage%20to%20cells.%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Kurpad%20said%20this%20could%20lead%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccardiac%20damage%2C%20liver%20fibrosis%2C%20gonadal%20dysfunction%2C%20and%20growth%20retardation%2C%20among%20many%20others%E2%80%9D%20for%20such%20individuals.%20Dr%20Kurpad%20further%20said%20that%20the%20storage%20form%20of%20iron%20%E2%80%93%20ferritin%20%E2%80%93%20would%20also%20increase%2C%20with%20increased%20rick%20of%20chronic%20diseases%20like%20diabetes.%20In%20the%20European%20Journal%20of%20Clinical%20Nutrition%2C%20Dr%20Kurpad%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41430-022-01222-2%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshowed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20this%20was%20linked%20to%20increased%20risks%20among%20adolescents%20of%20non-communicable%20disease.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20must%20be%20a%20mechanism%20for%20the%20problem%20of%20balancing%20the%20risks%20and%20benefits%20of%20iron%20supplementation%20in%20these%20areas%20%E2%80%93%20there%20is%20no%20shortcut%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecriticism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20activists%20and%20academics%2C%20the%20food%20safety%20regulator%2C%20FSSAI%20in%20August%202021%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fssai.gov.in%2Fupload%2Fuploadfiles%2Ffiles%2FCompendium_Food_Fortification_Regulations_30_09_2021.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eissued%20a%20gazette%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20adding%20%E2%80%9Cpersons%20with%20Sickle%20Cell%20Anemia%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20language%20of%20its%20fortification%20regulations%20of%202018%2C%20advising%20them%20not%20to%20consume%20%E2%80%9Ciron%20fortified%20products%E2%80%9D.%20Taking%20no%20responsibility%20to%20ensure%20this%2C%20it%20left%20it%20to%20already%20overburdened%20health%20departments%20in%20states%20to%20identify%20and%20protect%20such%20persons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20mid-2021%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1744094%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eset%20up%20a%20Sickle%20Cell%20Disease%20Support%20Corner%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Piramal%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20Piramal%20Swasthya%20Management%20and%20Research%20Institute%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccreate%20a%20database%20of%20individuals%20with%20sickle%20cell%20disease%2C%20or%20traits%20in%20the%20tribal%20population%E2%80%9D.%20Under%20this%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1953322%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20is%20carrying%20out%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a%20%E2%80%9Cuniversal%20screening%20of%207%20crore%20people%20in%20the%20age%20group%20of%200-40%20years%20in%20affected%20tribal%20areas%E2%80%9D.%20Piramal%20Foundation%20is%20the%20philanthropy%20arm%20of%20US%20%24%204%20billion-worth%20Piramal%20Group%20of%20Companies.%20The%20Swiss%20pharmaceutical%2C%20Hoffman-La%20Roche%20Ltd.%2C%20which%20was%20then%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20multinational%20company%20making%20synthetic%20vitamins%20had%20sold%20its%20India%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.joc.com%2Farticle%2Fhoffmann-la-roche-sells-stake-india-venture-piramal_19931104.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebusiness%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20majority%20stakes%20to%20Piramal.%20Piramal%20Group%20includes%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piramalpharmasolutions.com%2Fnutrition-solutions%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enutraceutical%20business%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20manufacturing%20synthetic%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortification.fssai.gov.in%2Fassets%2Ffile%2FCentral_License_Premix.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20among%20the%20suppliers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20factory-made%20nutrients%20in%20the%20government%20fortification%20programme.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPublic%20health%20experts%20expressed%20wariness%20at%20the%20involvement%20of%20nutraceutical-funded%20entities%20which%20advocated%20for%20the%20mandatory%20fortification%20of%20staples%2C%20and%20they%20questioned%20the%20ethics%20of%20such%20a%20mass%20screening%20of%20millions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20mass%2C%20universal%20screening%20for%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia%20raises%20ethical%20concerns%20because%20youth%20diagnosed%20with%20it%20may%20face%20discrimination%20in%20jobs%2C%20marriage%20and%20so%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Yogesh%20Jain%2C%20a%20community%20physician%20who%20has%20treated%20sickle%20cell%20disease%20patients%20in%20rural%20Adivasi%20areas%20in%20north%20Chhattisgarh.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20may%20be%20good%20to%20ensure%20complete%20diagnosis%20to%20those%20who%20are%20symptomatic%2C%20and%20once%20achieved%2C%20screen%20pregnant%20women%2C%20or%20newborns.%20Once%20that%20is%20done%2C%20you%20may%20consider%20mass%20screening%20after%20consulting%20with%20all%20communities%20and%20be%20ethically%20correct.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr%20Jain%20added%20that%20he%20did%20not%20view%20mandatory%20iron%20fortification%20of%20rice%20as%20a%20cure%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20anaemic%20population%2C%20because%20nutritional%20deficiency%20is%20the%20cause%20of%2060%25%20of%20all%20anaemia%20and%20iron%20deficiency%20is%20the%20cause%20of%20two-thirds%20of%20nutrition%20deficiency.%20Thus%2C%20iron%20deficiency%20anaemia%20constitutes%20the%20cause%20in%20less%20than%20half%20of%20all%20anaemia%20cases%2C%20the%20other%20causes%20being%20inflammation%2C%20or%20infections.%20%E2%80%9CLarge%20scale%20food%20fortification%20is%20a%20rent-seeking%20approach%20shrouded%20as%20a%20technological%20fix%2C%20where%20companies%20profit%20from%20making%20and%20blending%20nutrients.%20How%20will%20it%20help%3F%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Jain.%20%E2%80%9CI%20believe%20fortified%20rice%20in%20this%20form%20does%20not%20even%20adequately%20help%20the%20iron-deficient.%20It%20is%20corroborated%20by%20studies%20that%20food-based%20corrections%2C%20such%20as%20providing%20iron%20in%20the%20diet%20along%20with%20a%20fruit%2C%20would%20be%20better.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071251%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.12.12.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071251%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.12.12.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071251%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.12.12-300x210.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071251%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.12.12-1024x715.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685623%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22838%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPublic%20health%20experts%20say%20access%20to%20eating%20fresh%2C%20diverse%20foods%20such%20as%20citrus%20fruits%20will%20help%20an%20individual%20in%20better%20absorbing%20iron%20from%20food%20sources.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20government%20appointed%20PATH%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%20partner%E2%80%9D%20in%20Jharkhand%20to%20help%20implement%20the%20scheme.%C2%A0%20PATH%20is%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cproduct%20development%20organisation%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20initiated%20by%20Ford%20Foundation%20in%201977%2C%20which%20is%20heavily%20funded%20by%20the%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20with%20which%20it%20has%20long%20standing%20institutional%20ties.%20In%201998%2C%20before%20the%20official%20establishment%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20Gates%20created%20the%20Bill%20%26amp%3B%20Melinda%20Gates%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Vaccine%20Programme%20with%20a%20donation%20of%20%24100%20million%20and%20this%20was%20administered%20by%20PATH%E2%80%99s%20secretariat%20in%20Seattle.%20As%20per%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2022%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20financial%20report%2C%2043%25%20of%20its%20funding%20was%20from%20one%20private%20foundation%2C%20and%2032%25%20from%20United%20States%20government%20agencies.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20this%20was%2048%25%20and%2023%25%20respectively.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202010%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Findian-parliament-comes-down-hard-cervical-cancer-trial%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehalted%20a%20trial%20by%20PATH%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(funded%20by%20the%20Gates%20Foundation)%20among%20Adivasi%20children%2C%20in%20which%20it%20was%20testing%20vaccines%20against%20cervical%20cancer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhsrii.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2014%2F07%2F72.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2013%20report%20by%20the%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20health%20found%20collusion%20between%20Indian%20health%20regulators%20and%20PATH%20to%20downplay%20the%20violations%20in%20this%20vaccine%20trial.%20It%20found%20that%20PATH%20had%20described%20the%20project%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cobservational%20study%E2%80%9D%20and%20circumvented%20rules%20around%20such%20trials%2C%20such%20as%20reporting%20of%20serious%20adverse%20effects%20within%20a%20specific%20time.%20The%20parliamentary%20enquiry%20found%20that%20PATH%20had%20violated%20children%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20It%20had%20collected%20data%20on%20a%20large%20population%20of%2023%2C500%20children%20of%20age%2010%20to%2014.%20In%20the%20case%20of%205%2C000%20children%2C%20the%20parents%2Fguardians%20were%20not%20literate%20and%20could%20not%20even%20sign%20in%20their%20local%20language%2C%20in%20Telugu%20or%20Gujarati%2C%20and%20in%20Andhra%2C%20had%20simply%20obtained%20the%20consent%20from%20hostel%20wardens%20of%20residential%20schools%20the%20Adivasi%20children%20were%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piramalswasthya.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FSwasthya-FCRA-returns-Q2-FY-23-24.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elatest%20financial%20documents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20website%20of%20the%20Piramal%20Swasthya%20Management%20and%20Research%20Institute%2C%20which%20is%20running%20a%20%E2%80%9Csupport%20corner%E2%80%9D%20for%20sickle%20cell%20disease%20and%20is%20tasked%20with%20creating%20a%20database%20of%20individuals%20with%20sickle%20disease%20or%20traits%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20tribal%20population%2C%20in%20the%20financial%20quarter%20July%20to%20September%202023%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20donated%20to%20it%20Rs%2018%20crore%20as%20a%20grant%2C%20and%20PATH%20gave%20it%20a%20grant%20of%20Rs%201.4%20crore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EActivists%20critiqued%20the%20conflict%20of%20interest%20inherent%20in%20these%20policies.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20situation%20where%20the%20for-profit%20entity%20of%20the%20business%20is%20first%20supplying%20the%20fortificant%20earning%20profits%2C%20and%20the%20not-for-profit%20part%20of%20the%20same%20entity%20is%20managing%20the%20potential%20health%20harms%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Soumik%20Banerjee%2C%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20RTF%20and%20the%20Alliance%20for%20Sustainable%20and%20Holistic%20Agriculture%20(ASHA)%20fact-finding%20report%20on%20the%20scheme%20in%20Chhattisgarh.%20Referring%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20delayed%20advisory%20for%20those%20with%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia%20to%20avoid%20eating%20fortified%20rice%2C%20he%20called%20mandatory%20fortification%20%E2%80%9Ca%20wasteful%20strategy%20for%20the%20most%2C%20while%20potentially%20harmful%20for%20a%20few.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071444%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.14.06.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071444%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.14.06.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071444%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.14.06-300x191.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21071444%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-7.14.06-1024x652.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685624%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22764%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHealth%20and%20food%20activists%20say%20the%20scheme%20will%20help%20multinationals%20earn%20profits%20in%20selling%20micronutrients%2C%20but%20not%20address%20the%20crisis%20of%20undernourishment.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CFood%20fortification%20has%20been%20sometimes%20used%20as%20a%20temporary%20measure.%20But%20in%20pushing%20to%20make%20it%20mandatory%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20public%20schemes%2C%20these%20foundations%20and%20multi-nationals%20are%20simply%20creating%20new%20markets%2C%20while%20undermining%20smallholder%20farmers%20and%20their%20diets.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPiramal%20Swasthya%20Management%20and%20Research%20Institute%20and%20the%20Piramal%20Foundation%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20an%20emailed%20questionnaire%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20PATH%20official%20administering%20the%20programme%20who%20declined%20to%20be%20identified%20in%20the%20report%20said%20the%20criticism%20was%20exaggerated.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20critics%20are%20wrong.%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20there%20is%20evidence%20that%20fortified%20rice%20will%20address%20anaemia%2C%20on%20the%20other%2C%20in%20India%2C%20it%20is%20being%20done%20such%20that%20it%20would%20meet%20only%2025%25%20of%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20recommended%20dietary%20allowance%2C%20thus%2C%20there%20is%20very%20little%20scope%20of%20toxicity%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20these%20critics%20say%20that%20individuals%20are%20at%20risk%2C%20if%20the%20exact%20number%20of%20those%20with%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia%20is%20not%20even%20known%2C%20then%20where%20are%20they%20getting%20data%20to%20ask%20such%20questions%20from%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20clear.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Gates%20Foundation%20and%20PATH%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20an%20emailed%20questionnaire%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20advocacy%20for%20mandatory%20fortification%2C%20the%20experimentation%20and%20its%20potential%20side%20effects%20on%20vulnerable%20populations%2C%20including%20those%20with%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98How%20can%20we%20eat%20it%20when%20the%20birds%20don%E2%80%99t%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJawahar%2C%20a%20social%20activist%20in%20Palamu%2C%20questioned%20why%20fortified%20rice%20had%20been%20mandatory.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20it%20is%20harmful%20for%20some%20group%20of%20people%2C%20such%20as%20those%20with%20thalassemia%20or%20sickle%20cell%20disease%2C%20why%20is%20it%20being%20given%20to%20anyone%20at%20all%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%20He%20said%20there%20was%20little%20social%20acceptance%20of%20the%20new%20grains%20even%20months%20after%20they%20had%20been%20introduced%2C%20and%20several%20questions%20remained.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20people%20wonder%20why%20isn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%9Cplastic%20rice%E2%80%9D%20being%20given%20in%20the%20open%20market%2C%20why%20only%20as%20government%20ration%3F%20Some%20eat%20it.%20But%20I%20would%20say%20about%20half%20do%20not.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%20