20AI%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20happy%20about%20it.%20We%20want%20stability%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ryan%20Steelberg%2C%20CEO%20of%20Veritone%2C%20a%20company%20that%20helps%20firms%20develop%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20OpenAI%20becoming%20the%20new%20Apple%20or%20Google%2C%20the%20harsh%20critics%20see%20a%20deeply%20troubled%20startup%20that%20fell%20victim%20to%20the%20pearl-clutching%20of%20an%20incompetent%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20reached%20this%20point%20because%20minuscule%20risks%20have%20been%20hysterically%20amplified%20by%20the%20exotic%20thinking%20of%20sci-fi%20mindsets%2C%20and%20clickbait%20journalism%20from%20the%20press%2C%26quot%3B%20veteran%20venture%20capitalist%20Vinod%20Khosla%2C%20an%20early%20investor%20in%20OpenAI%2C%20wrote%20in%20The%20Information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Fallible%20people'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20observers%20warned%20that%20the%20drama%20in%20San%20Francisco%20proved%20that%20AI%20was%20too%20vital%20to%20be%20left%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20its%20creators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20important%20reminder%20that%20as%20brilliant%20as%20the%20designers%20of%20tech%20like%20AI%20--%20scientists%20or%20engineers%20--%20are%2C%20they%20are%20still%20just%20fallible%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Paul%20Barrett%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20the%20NYU%20Stern%20Center%20for%20Business%20and%20Human%20Rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20why%20it%20is%20important%20not%20to%20just%20defer%20to%20them%20on%20a%20technology%20that%20everyone%20agrees%20has%20significant%20risks%20even%20as%20it%20promises%20tremendous%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGary%20Marcus%2C%20a%20respected%20AI%20expert%2C%20said%20OpenAI's%20civil%20war%20%26quot%3Bhighlights%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20can't%20really%20trust%20the%20companies%20to%20self-regulate%20AI%20where%20even%20their%20own%20internal%20governance%20can%20be%20deeply%20conflicted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernment%20regulation%2C%20notably%20by%20the%20tougher-minded%20European%20Union%2C%20was%20needed%20more%20than%20ever%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20was%20actually%20created%20in%202015%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20being%20a%20counterweight%20to%20Google%2C%20which%20was%20by%20far%20the%20leader%20in%20developing%20AI%20technologies%20that%20mimic%20the%20operations%20of%20the%20human%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20nothing%20is%20known%20for%20sure%2C%20assumptions%20are%20rife%20that%20Altman's%20increased%20efforts%20to%20monetize%20the%20company's%20leading%20GPT-4%20model%2C%20all%20while%20keeping%20its%20inner%20functioning%20a%20secret%2C%20was%20becoming%20too%20problematic%20for%20the%20company's%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20several%20senior%20staff%20at%20OpenAI%20deserted%20the%20enterprise%20in%202021%20to%20build%20rival%20Anthropic%20over%20concerns%20that%20Altman%20was%20moving%20ahead%20too%20recklessly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'OpenAI%20is%20done'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20are%20shocked%20that%20the%20board%20had%20the%20power%20it%20did%2C%20or%20were%20naive%20enough%20to%20think%20they%20could%20actually%20use%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20of%20those%20board%20members%20are%20thought%20to%20have%20connections%20to%20the%20effective%20altruism%20movement%2C%20which%20frets%20over%20the%20risks%20of%20AI%2C%20but%20that%20critics%20say%20is%20cut%20off%20from%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhatever%20their%20beliefs%2C%20by%20Monday%20the%20board%20were%20overseeing%20a%20company%20in%20name%20only%2C%20with%20virtually%20the%20whole%20staff%20committed%20to%20a%20pledge%20of%20quitting%20the%20firm%20for%20Altman's%20project%20at%20Microsoft%20if%20the%20board%20refused%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnless%20OpenAI%20can%20block%20those%20departures%2C%20OpenAI%20is%20pretty%20much%20done%20at%20this%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20analyst%20Rob%20Enderle%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20mean%20a%20history-making%20victory%20for%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20has%20already%20seen%20its%20share%20price%20reach%20record%20levels%20over%20its%20ties%20to%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20like%20the%20best%20possible%20scenario%20for%20them%2C%20and%20the%20OpenAI%20board%20I%20am%20sure%20is%20kicking%20itself.%20They%20were%20clearly%20detached%20from%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Carolina%20Milanesi%2C%20analyst%20at%20Creative%20Strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700532300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fvq9eo47k_sam-altman-reuters_625x300_19_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fopenai-pretty-much-done-say-experts-as-staff-threatens-to-leave-ai-firm-4591055%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OpenAI%20has%20gone%20from%20ruling%20the%20world%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20with%20ChatGPT%20to%20chaos%2C%20its%20chief%20executive%20ousted%20seemingly%20for%20advancing%20too%20fast%20and%20too%20far%20with%20the%20risky%20technology.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fopenai-pretty-much-done-say-experts-as-staff-threatens-to-leave-ai-firm-4591055%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fopenai-pretty-much-done-say-experts-as-staff-threatens-to-leave-ai-firm-4591055%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fopenai-pretty-much-done-say-experts-as-staff-threatens-to-leave-ai-firm-4591055%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cricket%20Mata%20Ki%20Jai%3A%20Jingoism%20Lost%20i