%20the%202012%20version.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20USDA%20updated%20its%20map%20of%20plant%20hardiness%20zones%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20over%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20map%20shows%20that%20half%20the%20country%20has%20shifted%20to%20warmer%20zones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20updated%20zones%20could%20allow%20gardeners%20to%20grow%20plants%20that%20they%20never%20could%20before.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USDA%20has%20updated%20its%20plant%20hardiness%20zone%20map%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20over%2010%20years.%20The%20new%20map%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fgardening-qurantine-financial-independence-more-than-money-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echange%20how%20you%20garden%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGardening%20consultant%2C%20Megan%20London%2C%20for%20example%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F11%2F17%2F1213600629%2F-it-feels-like-im-not-crazy-gardeners-arent-surprised-as-usda-updates-key-map%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20she's%20now%20considering%20growing%20an%20array%20of%20new%20treats%20including%20kumquats%20and%20mandarin%20oranges%20in%20her%20gardens%20in%20central%20Arkansas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20new%20map%2C%20central%20Arkansas%20shifted%20half%20a%20zone%20up%20from%20zone%207b%20to%20zone%208a%20since%20the%20USDA%20last%20updated%20its%20map%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20are%20plant%20zones%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USDA's%20map%20is%20the%20national%20standard%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fgardening-tools-for-beginners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elets%20gardeners%20and%20growers%20know%3C%2Fa%3E%20what%20types%20of%20perennial%20plants%20%E2%80%94%20plants%20that%20return%20year%20after%20year%20%E2%80%94%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20thrive%20in%20certain%20locations.%20The%20map%20categorizes%20these%20locations%20by%20zones%20and%20half%20zones%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplanthardiness.ars.usda.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20USDA%20said%20on%20its%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20divided%20into%2013%20growing%20zones.%20Each%20zone%20represents%20the%20average%20lowest%20winter%20temperature%20an%20area%20typically%20sees%20every%20year%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplanthardiness.ars.usda.gov%2Fpages%2Fhow-to-use-the-maps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSDA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20chunk%20of%20southern%20Florida%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20zone%2010b%20(35%20to%2040%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%20while%20northern%20Montana%20has%20pockets%20of%20zone%203b%20(-35%20to%20-30%20degrees%20Fahrenheit).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20plants%20native%20to%20the%20US%20are%20equipped%20to%20survive%20in%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20zones%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhg.com%2Fgardening%2Fgardening-by-region%2Fhow-to-use-hardiness-zone-information%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBetter%20Homes%20%26amp%3B%20Gardens%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhg.com%2Fgardening%2Fflowers%2Fperennials%2Ftough-perennials-that-grow-in-dry-shade%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eferns%20and%20grasses%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20thrive%20in%20zones%204%20through%209%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20all%20about%20winter%20cold%2C%20this%20map%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Daly%2C%20director%20of%20the%20PRISM%20Climate%20Group%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20planting%20zones%20in%20terms%20of%20when%20you%20plant%20or%20what%20can%20survive%20the%20summer.%26quot%3B%20He%20helped%20develop%20the%20map%20along%20with%20the%20USDA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHalf%20of%20the%20US%20has%20shifted%20to%20warmer%20plant%20zones%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Southeastern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd74922cf74a5739a7e1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECentral%20and%20northern%20Florida%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20Southeastern%20US%20have%20changed%20zones%20on%20the%202023%20map%20(top).%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20map%20for%202023%20has%20pushed%20half%20the%20country%20into%20a%20warmer%20half%20zone%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20has%20remained%20in%20the%20same%20zone%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ars.usda.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fresearch-news%2F2023%2Fusda-unveils-updated-plant-hardiness-zone-map%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20USDA%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Northeastern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd0b64ca513d8242c8c12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202023%20USDA%20map%20shows%20warmer%20zones%20in%20central%20Michigan%2C%20as%20well%20as%20shifts%20in%20some%20Northeastern%20states.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20some%20areas%20of%20Omaha%2C%20Nebraska%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flancaster.unl.edu%2Fhort%2Fmastergardener%2Fresources%2FNE%2520USDA%2520Plan%2520Hardiness%2520Zone%2520Map.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20moved%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%205b%20to%206a.%20Meaning%20that%20the%20average%20lowest%20winter%20temperature%20for%20that%20region%20rose%20from%20between%20-15%20and%20-10%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20to%20-10%20to%20-5%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%2C%20side-by-side%2C%20showing%20the%20USDA%20Plant%20Hardiness%20Zones%20in%20North%20Central%20US%20in%202023%20and%202012%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bcf659c7d23cb3b9db793%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20North%20Central%20US%2C%20some%20of%20the%20coldest%20zones%20have%20disappeared%20from%20northern%20Minnesota%20in%202023%20(left)%20compared%20to%202012%20(right).%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20could%20mean%20a%20shift%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuilt-side-business-plant-kween-social-media-heres-how-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20will%20grow%20best%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20your%20garden.%20When%20you're%20purchasing%20perennials%2C%20you'll%20often%20see%20their%20zone%20ranges%20listed%2C%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20growers%20should%20be%20cautious%2C%20Jonathan%20Foster%2C%20a%20horticulture%20outreach%20professional%2C%20wrote%20on%20The%20University%20of%20Maine's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fextension.umaine.edu%2Fgardening%2Fmanual%2Fusda-plant-hardiness-zone-map%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaine%20Gardner%20Manual%3C%2Fa%3E%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELimitations%20of%20the%20USDA's%20new%20plant%20zone%20map%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20map%20is%20a%20guideline%2C%20not%20a%20guarantee%2C%26quot%3B%20Foster%20wrote%2C%20and%20plants%20can%20thrive%20in%20several%20zones.%20However%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20consider%20other%20factors%2C%20like%20summer%20temperatures%20and%20soil%20quality%20as%20well.%20The%20map%20doesn't%20reflect%20these%20nuances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Southwestern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd6b422cf74a5739a7dbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20zone%20shifts%20in%20the%20Southwestern%20US%20for%20the%202023%20map%20(top)%20aren't%20as%20widespread%20as%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20country.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFoster%20also%20noted%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhouseplant-care-products%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20delicate%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20poppies%2C%20might%20not%20fare%20as%20well%20as%20hardier%20trees%20and%20shrubs%20in%20snowy%20climates%20like%20Maine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20map%20is%20also%20limited%20in%20how%20detailed%20it%20can%20get%2C%20Daly%20said.%20Your%20garden%20might%20get%20more%20sun%20than%20your%20neighbors%20or%20have%20shadier%20spots%20thanks%20to%20trees.%20%26quot%3BThose%20may%20have%20microclimates%20that%20are%20warmer%20or%20colder%20than%20what%20the%20zone%20says%20that%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20caused%20half%20the%20US%20to%20shift%20to%20a%20warmer%20zone%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USDA%20said%20that%20the%20shift%20to%20warmer%20zones%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20necessarily%20reflective%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-crisis-comedians-jokes-drive-change-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20several%20factors%20contributed%20to%20the%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side-by-side%20maps%20showing%20the%202023%20(left)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Northwestern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd1cf4ca513d8242c8d91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20Northwestern%20US%2C%20the%202023%20USDA%20map%20(left)%20shows%20some%20regions%20of%20Montana%20in%20new%2C%20warmer%20zones.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDaly%20and%20the%20USDA%20used%20data%20from%201991%20to%202020%20and%20chose%20the%20coldest%20night%20of%20the%20year.%20%26quot%3BWe%20only%20have%2030%20numbers%20that%20we're%20averaging%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%20That's%20why%20it's%20important%20to%20look%20at%20decades%20of%20data%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20temperature%20on%20the%20coldest%20night%20can%20shift%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%20aside%20from%20climate%20change.%20One%20year%20might%20not%20have%20a%20cold%20snap%2C%20and%20the%20next%20winter's%20could%20be%20particularly%20harsh%2C%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20map%20is%20also%20based%20on%20information%20from%20thousands%20more%20weather%20stations%2C%20according%20to%20the%20USDA.%20It%20pulled%20data%20from%2013%2C412%20weather%20stations%20compared%20to%207%2C983%20for%20the%202012%20map%2C%20per%20the%20USDA's%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaly%20developed%20Prism%2C%20the%20software%20that%20created%20the%20map.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20good%20at%20reproducing%20the%20effects%20of%20features%20on%20the%20Earth's%20surface%2C%20such%20as%20mountains%2C%20valleys%2C%20and%20coastlines%2C%20on%20climatic%20patterns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It%20helped%20make%20the%20map%20more%20detailed%20and%20accurate%20than%20previous%20versions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20interactive.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20enter%20your%20zip%20code%20or%20you%20can%20click%20anywhere%20in%20the%20map%20and%20zoom%20and%20pan%20on%20it%20and%20see%20what%20your%20zone%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20climate%20change%20is%20influencing%20plant%20hardiness%20zones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20grand%20scheme%20of%20things%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20influencing%20where%20plants%20can%20grow%2C%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side-by-side%20maps%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20South%20Central%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd2904ca513d8242c8efa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESections%20of%20the%20South%20Central%20US%2C%20including%20Houston%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20New%20Orleans%2C%20Louisiana%2C%20have%20changed%20to%20new%20zones%20in%20the%202023%20USDA%20map%20(left).%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20for%20a%20fact%20that%20average%20temperatures%20are%20rising%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%20There's%20no%20doubt%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20this%20should%20cause%20plant%20hardiness%20zones%20to%20gradually%20shift%20northward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusda-unveils-first-new-plant-zone-hardiness-map-over-decade-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700531142000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bcdc49c7d23cb3b9db614%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusda-unveils-first-new-plant-zone-hardiness-map-over-decade-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22USDA%20unveils%20its%20new%20plant%20zone%20hardiness%20map.%20Half%20of%20the%20country%20has%20moved%