99s%20recent%20book%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fdisplay%2Ftitle%2F62356%3Flanguage%3Den%5C%22%3EThe%20Rise%20of%20the%20Capital-State%20and%20Neo-Nationalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20which%20attempts%20to%20provide%20a%20political%20economy%20approach%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20%E2%80%98neo-nationalism%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20a%20populist%20form%20of%20nationalism%20observed%20in%20the%20contemporary%20globalised%20period.%20Read%20the%20first%20part%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fhow-neo-nationalism-has-fuelled-the-transformation-of-old-welfare-state-to-new-capital-state%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20own%20book%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3EStrongmen%20Saviours%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20our%20comparative%20political%20economy%20analysis%20in%20explaining%20the%20recent%20wave%20of%20right-wing%20populist%20movements%20across%20the%20world%20was%20explained%20through%20a%20distinct%20pattern%20exhibiting%20features%20that%20have%20been%20unique%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20right-wing%20movements%20(as%20against%20left-wing%20movements%20of%20the%20past).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20purpose%20then%20was%20to%20provide%20a%20comparative%20socio-political%2C%20economic%20explanation%20of%20the%20rise%20of%20populist%20beliefs%20and%20anti-political%20elite%20sentiment%20that%20has%20not%20captured%20much%20of%20the%20Western%20and%20non-Western%20sphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pyramid%20constructed%20below%2C%20drawn%20from%20our%20book%E2%80%99s%20research%2C%20may%20offer%20some%20insights%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20181018%2FDM1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20181018%2FDM1.png%20720w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20181018%2FDM1-300x189.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685559%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22454%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Author%E2%80%99s%20graphic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conceptual%20pyramid%20attempts%20to%20unpack%20features%20of%20right-wing%20populism%2C%20operating%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98ideological%20populism%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(ideologically%20aligned%20populist%20movements)%2C%20which%20has%20a%20distinct%20meaning%20(see%20a%20more%20detailed%20explainer%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Flive%2FPgPnQ3RmdqA%3Ffeature%3Dshare%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20simple%20terms%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Eideological%20populism%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Erefers%20to%20the%20unchecked%20and%20unabated%20rise%20of%20an%20ideology%2C%20the%20marginalisation%20of%20its%20moderate%20factions%2C%20involving%20the%20development%20of%20a%20cult-personality%20that%20infuses%20shades%20of%20populism%20into%20it.%20Normatively%2C%20this%20can%20be%20ideologically%20aligned%20towards%20the%20%E2%80%98political%20left%E2%80%99%20or%20the%20%E2%80%98political%20right%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20distinct%20characteristics%20of%20%3Cem%3Erightwing%20%3C%2Fem%3Epopulism%20at%20least%20the%20way%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Ewe%20have%20observed%20in%20countries%20such%20as%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Russia%20and%20Brazil%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0did%20see%20certain%20common%20features%2C%20across%20different%20times%20and%20spaces.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Eexplained%20a%20few%20of%20these%20factors%2Ffeatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20pyramid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fright-wing-populism-towards-a-new-theory-of-economic-change%23read-more%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20three%20contributing%20drivers%20for%20the%20Right%E2%80%99s%20authoritative%20rise%20to%20majoritarian%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E1.%20Failure%20of%20neoliberalism%20(supply-side%20economics%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9990s)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20origins%20of%20each%20of%20these%20movements%20are%20sourced%20in%20the%20economic%20discontents%20of%20%E2%80%98neoliberalism%E2%80%99%20or%20the%20nature%20of%20supply-side%20economics%20(externally%20influenced%20by%20the%20West%2FWashington%20Consensus%20style%20reform%20packages)%20pursued%20in%20the%201990s.%20Studies%20from%20scholars%20like%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3ESides%20et%20al.%20(2018)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3ENorris%20%26amp%3B%20Inglehart%20(2019)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3EMargalit%20(2019)%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0also%20explain%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20wave%20of%20rise%20in%20religious%20conservatism%20or%20religious%20orthodoxy%20(from%20Hindutva%20to%20Orthodox%20Islam%20to%20Evangelical%20Catholicism)%20that%20aided%20the%20rise%20of%20each%20of%20the%20leaders%20who%20either%20belonged%20to%20political%20parties%20or%20to%20orthodox-religious%20based%20organisations%20which%20ensured%20an%20undercurrent%20of%20religious%20conservatism.%20I%20explain%20more%20about%20this%20phenomenon%20(as%20seen%20in%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20Brazil)%20in%20a%20lecture%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Flive%2FPgPnQ3RmdqA%3Ffeature%3Dshare%5C%22%3Egiven%20here.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trigger%20factor%20which%20led%20to%20the%20mass-protest%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20each%20strongman%20figure%20(from%20Modi%20to%20Bolsonaro)%2C%20was%20often%20related%20to%20either%20a%20series%20of%20big%20public%20corruption%20episodes%20or%20reported%20scandal(s)%20in%20the%20home%20country%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20political%20environment%2C%20which%20gave%20the%20opportunity%20for%20the%20mass-support%20in%20favour%20of%20an%20alternative%20imagination%20of%20%E2%80%98power%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20leader%2C%20someone%20outside%20the%20status%20quo%20ruling%20political%20elite-to%20come%20to%20power%2C%20and%20enjoy%20mass%20popularity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20India%20to%20Brazil%2C%20each%20of%20the%20countries%20we%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Ediscuss%20in%20the%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%20saw%20episodes%20of%20public%20corruption%20(via%20scandals)%20or%20were%20operating%20in%20a%20widely%20%E2%80%98perceived%20environment%20of%20corruption%E2%80%99%20that%20made%20more%20of%20the%20popular%20vote%20pivot%20towards%20the%20choice%20of%20voting%20for%20an%20%E2%80%98alternative%E2%80%99%20(as%20also%20seen%20with%20the%20protest%20vote%20for%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20the%202016%20US%20presidential%20election).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weaponisation%20of%20social%20media%20in%20a%20new%20tech-enabled%20information%20order%20made%20it%20possible%20for%20right-wing%20populists%20to%20continue%20feeding%20an%20alternative%2C%20post-truth%20rhetorical%20narrative%20(us%20vs%20them%20the%20axis%20of%20immigration)%20which%20not%20only%20helped%20them%20and%20their%20parties%20to%20constantly%20gain%20the%20support%20of%20a%20polarised%20%E2%80%98majority%E2%80%99%20(their%20own%20voter%20base)%2C%20but%20also%20help%20them%20sustain%2Fconsolidate%20and%20then%20later%20centralise%20power%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20others%20(those%20in%20minorities).%20Surveillance%20capitalism%20made%20this%20possible%20too%20under%20a%20new%20nexus%20of%20private%20capital-state%20relationship%20which%20supported%20%E2%80%98strongmen%E2%80%99%20figures%20in%20power%20through%20social%20media%20and%20digitised%20surveillance%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E2.%20Focus%20on%20privatisation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nature%20of%20fiscal%20policy%20and%20the%20fiscal%20choice%20made%20by%20each%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Estrongmen%20figures%20(right-wing%20populists)%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20been%20drastically%20varied%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20earlier%20regimes%20of%20populist%20movements%20(as%20seen%20say%20in%20Latin%20America)%20where%20strongmen%20leadership%20was%20influenced%20by%20a%20theory%20of%20economic%20and%20political%20change%20belonging%20to%20pro-welfare%2C%20left-leaning%20policies%20(which%20in%20some%20instances%20like%20Venezuela%20made%20governments%20fiscally%20indebted).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20variant%20of%20right-wing%20populism%20has%20seen%20a%20promotion%20of%20privatisation%20(a%20reorientation%20of%20previous%20state-private%20capital%20elite%20relationship)%20%E2%80%93%20pursued%20with%20gradual%20disinvestment%20of%20public%20assets%2C%20government%20ownership%20of%20resources%20(including%20a%20de-funding%20of%20social%20programmes%20targeted%20for%20areas%20of%20job%20creation%2C%20human%20capital%20development-healthcare%20and%20education).%20This%20is%20widely%20seen%20in%20the%20fiscal%20choices%20made%20by%20most%20strongmen%20figures%20(case%20in%20point%3A%20see%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20term%20of%20governance%20in%20India).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20they%20(strongmen)%20continue%20to%20strike%20a%20chord%20with%20extremely%20low-income%20voters%20in%20some%20of%20the%20lesser%20developed%20states%2Fprovinces%20by%20the%20deployed%20political%20use%20of%20specific%20targeted-beneficiary-based%20%E2%80%98welfare%20schemes%E2%80%99%20(say%2C%20free%20nutrition)%20to%20keep%20the%20more%20poor%20content%20and%20as%20part%20of%20a%20loyal%20voter%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20however%20be%20observed%20that%20none%20of%20this%20so-called%20%E2%80%98welfare%E2%80%99%20spending%20is%20aimed%20at%20the%20upward%20mobility%20of%20the%20low-income%20beneficiary%20(say%20through%20complementary%20support%20offered%20in%20human%20capital%20development%20%E2%80%93%20education%2C%20healthcare%20or%20job%20support%20plans).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E3.%20On%20contestations%20within%3A%20Hyper-globalism%20and%20ideological%20populism%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDani%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20recent%20work%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3E2021%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrodrik.scholar.harvard.edu%2Fsites%2Fscholar.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Fdani-rodrik%2Ffiles%2Fon_productivism.pdf%5C%22%3E2023%3C%2Fa%3E)%20offers%20useful%20insights%20on%20at%20least%20addressing%20one%20of%20these%20%E2%80%98contested%E2%80%99%20conceptual%20questions%3A%20Why%20did%20globalisation%20of%20the%20post-1990s%20variant%20fuel%20a%20certain%20wave%20of%20populism%20(one%20that%20spread%20far%20across%20the%20west%20and%20the%20east)%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20this%20one%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Rodrik%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20what%20are%20the%20mechanisms%20through%20which%20globalization%20fuels%20populism.%20Answering%20this%20question%20requires%20a%20fully%20fleshed-out%20model%20of%20political%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESecond%2C%20globalization%20is%20not%20just%20one%20thing%3A%20We%20can%20distinguish%20between%20international%20trade%2C%20international%20finance%2C%20and%20international%20labor%20flows%2C%20specifically.%20How%20does%20each%20one%20of%20these%20facets%20of%20globalization%20work%20its%20way%20through%20the%20political%20system%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThird%2C%20globalization%20is%20clearly%20not%20the%20only%20economic%20shock%20that%20creates%20redistributive%20effects%20or%20economic%20anxiety%E2%80%94and%20it%20may%20not%20even%20be%20the%20most%20important%20one.%20Why%20does%20globalization%20appear%20to%20have%20an%20outsized%20effect%20on%20politics%20compared%20to%2C%20say%2C%20technological%20change%20or%20regular%20business%20cycles%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20aspects%20are%20studied%20more%20empirically%20by%20Rodrik%20in%20the%20framework%20created%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20450px)%2085vw%2C%20450px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20195700%2FDM2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20195700%2FDM2.png%20626w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20195700%2FDM2-300x284.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685580%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22426%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20according%20to%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20analytical%20framework%20above%2C%20and%20most%20directly%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eeconomic%20dislocation%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0can%20determine%20voters%E2%80%99%20preferences%20for%20policies%20and%20leaders%20(arrow%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ea%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Voters%20in%20a%20region%20where%20employment%20prospects%20have%20been%20adversely%20affected%20by%20a%20rise%20in%20imports%20may%20choose%20to%20cast%20their%20vote%20for%20a%20politician%20who%20advocates%20protectionism%20and%20a%20tougher%20line%20against%20foreign%20exporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20economic%20dislocation%20may%20shape%20voters%E2%80%99%20preferences%20indirectly%20through%20the%20effect%20it%20has%20on%20identity%20or%20the%20salience%20of%20certain%20cultural%20values%20(arrow%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eb%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Concretely%2C%20economic%20shocks%20can%20heighten%20feelings%20of%20insecurity%2C%20inducing%20voters%20to%20make%20sharper%20distinctions%20between%20insiders%20(%E2%80%9Cus%E2%80%9D)%20and%20ethnic%2C%20religious%2C%20or%20racial%20outsiders%20(%E2%80%9Cthem%E2%80%9D).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20lead%20voters%20to%20yearn%20for%20an%20earlier%20era%20of%20prosperity%20and%20stability%2C%20increasing%20the%20political%20salience%20of%20traditional%20cultural%20values%20and%20hierarchies.%20And%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20generate%20wider%20economic%20and%20social%20gaps%20within%20a%20nation%2C%20economic%20shocks%20may%20reinforce%20more%20local%2C%20less%20encompassing%20identities.%20To%20the%20extent%20that%20such%20effects%20operate%2C%20political%20preferences%20that%20appear%20to%20be%20driven%20by%20cultural%20values%20do%20in%20fact%20have%20deeper%20economic%20roots.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Eexplored%20some%20of%20these%20links%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20discontents%20of%20neoliberal%20economics%20and%20populism%20in%20the%20context%20of%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Brazil%20and%20Russia%3B%20however%2C%20there%20were%20other%20factors%20complementing%20this%20%E2%80%93%20and%20to%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20framework%20shared%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20additional%20causal%20factors%3A%20instances%20of%20large-scale%20public%20corruption%20(or%20an%20environment%20of%20perceived%20corrupt%20political%20elite)%2C%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20religious%20conservatism%20contributed%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20right-wing%20populist%20movements%20that%20subsequently%20brought%20leaders%20like%20Modi%2C%20Bolsonaro%20and%20Putin%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Eis%20a%20critical%20need%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20put%20these%20explanations%20in%20both%20perspective%20and%20context%20while%20building%20upon%20what%20Gudavarthy%E2%80%99s%20and%20Oleksandr%E2%80%99s%20frame%20of%20reasoning%20brings%20in%20light%20by%20adopting%20a%20more%20neo-subaltern%20approach%20that%20is%20grounded%20in%20interpreting%20a%20random%20person%E2%80%99s%20influence%2Fpreference%20for%20the%20political%20right%20and%2For%20in%20explaining%20how%20the%20Right%20operates%20in%20influencing%20one%E2%80%99s%20everyday%20ethics%20%E2%80%93%20more%20distinctively%20and%20assertively%20%E2%80%93%20while%20thriving%20on%20the%20anxieties%2C%20fears%20and%20insecurities%20of%20the%20emotive%20majority%2C%20including%20those%20fuelled%20by%20negative%20emotions%20finding%20an%20agency%20of%20their%20own%20by%20Modi-Shah%E2%80%99s%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20in%20also%20understanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Ehow%20the%20moral-ethical%20core%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20an%20average%20Indian%20(a%20Hindu%20voter%20subscribing%20to%20the%20populist%20belief)%20remains%20influenced%20by%20the%20applied%20role%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3EDharam%2C%20Dharma%2C%20Kama%20and%20Karma%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20everyday%20life.%20A%20neo-subaltern%20ethnographic%20methodology%20may%20help%20explicate%20some%20of%20these%20new%20dimensions%20warranting%20a%20mixed-methods%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fmodi-adani-oligarchy-stock-offshore%5C%22%3Ethe%20conceptualisation%20of%20the%20new%20capital-state%E2%80%99s%20oligarghic%20rise%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20in%20India%2C%20is%20linked%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20change%20seen%20in%20the%20global%20technological%20application%20of%20information%20technology%2C%20rise%20of%20new%20media%20(via%20social%20media)%20that%20weaponised%20a%20counter-narrative%20for%20extreme%20forms%20of%20radicalism%20amongst%20the%20masses%2C%20interplaying%20with%20their%20discontented%20feelings%20about%20neoliberal%20economic%20policies%20(leaving%20many%20of%20them%20worse%20off)%2C%20the%20breakdown%20of%20the%20old%20welfare%20state%20(creating%20an%20erosion%20of%20access%20to%20basic%20amenities)%2C%20rising%20corruption%2C%20and%20a%20moralistic-vacuum%20created%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98material-acquisitioning%E2%80%99%20capitalistic%20landscape%20(triggering%20a%20rise%20of%20conservatism%2C%20orthodoxy%2C%20and%20desiring%20a%20new%20moral-ethical%20code%20for%20everyday%20politics%2Faction%20of%20%3Cem%3Ebeing%3C%2Fem%3E%20under%20an%20authoritarian-neonationalist%20regime).%20We%20need%20a%20more%20case-dependent%2Fsensitive%20analysis%20of%20bringing%20an%20interpretative%20thread%20to%20these%20complex%20factors%2C%20explaining%20not%20just%20the%20rise%20but%20sustenance%20of%20neonationalism%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20associate%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700530238000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F12140727%2FIMG_3148.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwhat-explains-the-political-rights-ascendancy-to-global-power%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Instances%20of%20large-scale%20public%20corruption%20(or%20an%20environment%20of%20perceived%20corrupt%20political%20elite)%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20religious%20conservatism%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20other%20factors%2C%20contributed%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20right-wing%20populist%20movements.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwhat-explains-the-political-rights-ascendancy-to-global-power%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ektaa%20rocks%20a%20fusion%20ensemble%20on%20Emmys%20red%20carpet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700530193000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105369252%2Cimgsize-62426.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Finternational-emmy-awards-ektaa-kapoor-adds-a-pop-of-colour-to-the-red-carpet-in-a-fusion-ethnic-ensemble%2Farticleshow%2F105368988.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105368988.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EFilmmaker%20Ektaa%20Kapoor%20looked%20stunning%20in%20a%20traditional%20ensemble%20as%20she%20attended%20the%2051st%20International%20Emmy%20Awards.%20Ektaa%20will%20be%20honored%20with%20the%20Directorate%20Award%20at%20the%20ceremony.%20She%20expressed%20her%20gratitude%20for