0legally%20obligated%20to%20adhere%20to%20such%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20declaration%20suggests%20Moscow%20may%20seek%20to%20refill%20its%20stocks%20with%20Iranian-made%20ballistic%20missiles.%20That%20could%20have%20ramifications%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20is%20preparing%20for%20another%20winter%20of%20Russian%20missile%20and%20drone%20attacks%20on%20civilian%20and%20military%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EUN%20Security%20Council%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsecuritycouncil%2Fcontent%2F2231%2Fbackground%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResolution%202231%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20passed%20in%20July%202015%2C%20days%20after%20the%20US%20and%20Iran%20agreed%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F2009-2017.state.gov%2Fe%2Feb%2Ftfs%2Fspi%2Firan%2Fjcpoa%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520July%252014%252C%25202015%252C%2520the%2Cprogram%2520will%2520be%2520exclusively%2520peaceful.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Iran%20nuclear%20deal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(The%20EU%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20China%20also%20signed%20the%20deal.)%20The%20resolution%20prohibited%20Tehran%20from%20exporting%20and%20importing%20missiles%20and%20drones%20with%20ranges%20exceeding%20186%20miles%20and%20payloads%20over%201%2C100%20pounds%20%E2%80%94%20limits%20suggested%20by%20the%20Missile%20Technology%20Control%20Regime%20%E2%80%94%20until%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20and%20the%20European%20signatories%20of%20the%20nuclear%20deal%20have%20decided%20to%20uphold%20sanctions%20against%20Iran's%20missile%20program%2C%20primarily%20because%20Tehran%20violated%20some%20terms%20of%20the%20agreement%20after%20Washington%20withdrew%20in%202018.%20They%20were%20also%20angered%20by%20Iran's%20decision%20to%20arm%20Russia%20with%20Shahed-131%20and%20-136%20one-way%20attack%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20Shahed-136%20Shahed-131%20drones%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655b96e922cf74a5739a30cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221386%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShahed-136%2C%20left%2C%20and%20Shahed-131%20drones%20on%20display%20at%20an%20IRGC%20facility%20in%20Tehran%20in%20October.%3Cp%3EMorteza%20Nikoubazl%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThere%20has%20been%20persistent%20speculation%20about%20Iran%20supplying%20Russia%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2022%2F12%2F12%2Fukraine-war-russia-missiles-iran-limit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshort-range%20ballistic%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20SRBMs%2C%20but%20that%20would%20almost%20certainly%20draw%20snapback%20sanctions%20under%20the%20resolution%20and%20Tehran%20has%20not%20yet%20done%20so.%20(While%20the%20ballistic-missile%20ban%20has%20expired%2C%20previous%20multilateral%20sanctions%20could%20be%20reimposed%20under%20a%20sunset%20clause%20option%20outlined%20under%202231%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F19%2Fhow-significant-is-lifting-of-un-curbs-on-irans-missile-programme%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremains%20in%20effect%20until%202025%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20Russian%20Foreign%20Ministry's%20statement%20on%20October%2017%20suggests%20Moscow%20may%20seek%20Iranian%20short-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20to%20bolster%20its%20arsenal%20for%20another%20winter%20of%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSupplies%20to%20and%20from%20Iran%20of%20products%20falling%20under%20the%20Missile%20Technology%20Control%20Regime%20no%20longer%20require%20prior%20approval%20by%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Frussia-says-it-need-no-longer-obey-un-restriction-missile-technology-iran-2023-10-17%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ERussia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-searching-for-missiles-to-attack-ukraine-wont-run-out-2023-7%5C%22%3Econtinues%20to%20produce%20its%20own%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20drones%2C%20but%20its%20constant%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine%20have%20strained%20its%20supplies.%20Last%20winter%2C%20when%20Moscow%20began%20using%20Iran's%20drones%2C%20it%20launched%201%2C000%20of%20them%20over%20six%20months%2C%20and%20Russian%20forces%20launched%20an%20estimated%20500%20drones%20against%20Ukrainian%20targets%20in%20September%20alone%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fthe-war-zone%2Fukraine-situation-report-kyiv-prepares-for-unprecedented-winter-drone-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20record%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIf%20Moscow%20gets%20Iranian%20SRBMs%20now%2C%20Ukraine%20could%20face%20unprecedented%20pressure%2C%20but%20there%20are%20still%20doubts%20those%20missiles%20will%20end%20up%20in%20Russian%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20Zolfaghar%20Basir%20Dezful%20ballistic%20missiles%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655b96e922cf74a5739a30d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221364%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIran's%20Zolfaghar%20Basir%2C%20top%2C%20and%20Dezful%20short-%20and%20medium-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20in%20Tehran%20in%20January%202022.%3Cp%3EMorteza%20Nikoubazl%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BFrankly%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20that%20the%20