tank%20gun%20of%20a%20Leopard%201%20A5%20main%20battle%20tank.%3Cp%3EKlaus-Dietmar%20Gabbert%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussia%20is%20advising%20troops%20to%20weld%20cages%20onto%20their%20vehicles%20and%20tanks%20to%20protect%20from%20drone%20attacks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENew%20illustrations%20show%20soldiers%20how%20to%20attach%20cages%20onto%20various%20vehicles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBoth%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20have%20previously%20employed%20cages%2C%20but%20the%20strategy%20now%20seems%20to%20be%20official%20Russian%20doctrine.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20issues%20protecting%20your%20tank%20from%20exploding%20drones%3F%20Russia's%20advice%3A%20Weld%20cages%20onto%20any%20and%20every%20vehicle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20illustrations%20released%20from%20Russia's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20detail%20that%20exact%20strategy%20to%20their%20troops%2C%20indicating%20how%20each%20vehicle%20should%20be%20covered%20with%20cages%20to%20protect%20from%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles%20(UAVs).%20Although%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20war%20have%20previously%20used%20crude%20cages%20to%20contend%20with%20drones%2C%20Russia%20is%20apparently%20resigning%20itself%20to%20these%20limited%20defenses%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future%20in%20a%20sign%20of%20how%20dominant%20and%20dangerous%20attack%20drones%20have%20become.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20illustrations%20from%20the%20ministry's%20main%20armored%20directorate%20were%20released%2C%20showing%20various%20methods%20for%20protecting%20equipment%20from%20first-person%20view%20(FPV)%20drones%20rigged%20with%20explosives%20and%20other%20UAV%20threats.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20ministry's%20official%20advice%20is%20to%20weld%20various%20shapes%20and%20sizes%20of%20cages%20to%20vehicles.%20Some%20illustrations%20show%20cages%20on%20top%20of%20tank%20turrets%2C%20while%20others%20show%20cages%20surrounding%20the