ons%20of%20transferring%20misappropriated%20amounts%20to%20the%20T.D.P.%20party%E2%80%99s%20account%2C%20no%20prima%20facie%20evidence%20is%20presented%20to%20support%20this%20claim.%20This%20court%20views%20that%20such%20serious%20allegations%20should%20be%20backed%20by%20substantial%20material%20before%20seeking%20the%20remand%20of%20the%20petitioner.%20The%20court%2C%20at%20this%20point%2C%20views%20the%20lack%20of%20supportive%20material%20as%20a%20gap%20in%20the%20investigation%E2%80%99s%20conclusion%20that%20the%20alleged%20misappropriated%20amount%20had%20been%20transferred%20to%20the%20T.D.P.%20party%E2%80%99s%20account.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20noted%20that%20Naidu%20could%20not%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20all%20the%20discrepancies%20noted%20in%20the%20forensic%20audit%20report%20as%20per%20which%20out%20of%20the%20Rs%20371%20crore%2C%20at%20least%20Rs%20241%20crore%20were%20misappropriated%20by%20SISW%20and%20Design%20Tech%20and%20diverted%20to%20various%20shell%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Prosecution%20needs%20to%20clarify%20how%20the%20petitioner%20can%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20such%20discrepancies%2C%20as%20it%20is%20not%20his%20duty%2C%20as%20the%20then%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20to%20verify%20and%20compare%20parties%E2%80%99%20signatures%E2%80%A6It%20remains%20to%20be%20clarified%20how%20the%20differences%20outlined%20in%20the%20report%20can%20be%20deemed%20the%20fundamental%20cause%20for%20the%20alleged%20misappropriation%20of%20funds%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20judge%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20October%2031%2C%20the%20court%20had%20granted%20Naidu%20four%20weeks%E2%80%99%20medical%20bail.%20He%20had%20been%20arrested%20by%20the%20CID%20on%20September%209%20and%20has%20been%20in%20the%20Rajahmundry%20central%20prison%20since%20September%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CID%20has%20listed%20Naidu%20as%20%E2%80%98accused%20number%20one%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20alleged%20skill%20development%20s