3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Knesset%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20parliament%2C%20is%20set%20to%20discuss%20a%20controversial%20draft%20law%20that%20would%20legalize%20executing%20Palestinian%20prisoners%2C%20Israeli%20National%20Security%20Minister%20Itamar%20Ben%20Gvir%20said%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Knesset%20will%20discuss%20on%20Monday%20preparations%20for%20the%20first%20reading%20of%20the%20death%20penalty%20law%20for%20Palestinian%20prisoners%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gvir%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EMaariv%3C%2Fem%3E%20newspaper.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20preliminary%20reading%20last%20March%2C%20the%20Knesset%20approved%20the%20draft%20law%20that%20would%20allow%20courts%20to%20impose%20the%20death%20penalty%20on%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20convicted%20of%20killing%20Israelis.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGvir%20leads%20the%20Otzma%20Yehudit%2C%20or%20Jewish%20Power%2C%20party%20that%20submitted%20the%20primary%20legislation%2C%20which%20was%20then%20supported%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20legislation%20was%20met%20with%20a%20wave%20of%20opposition%20by%20Palestinians.%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20militant%20group%20governing%20Gaza%2C%20said%20such%20policies%20would%20not%20stop%20Palestinians%20from%20exercising%20their%20right%20to%20resistance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Israeli%20regime%20detains%20more%20than%207%2C800%20Palestinians%20in%20its%20prisons%2C%20including%20some%20300%20children%20and%2072%20women%2C%20according%20to%20Qadura%20Fares%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20Commission%20for%20Prisoners%E2%80%99%20Affairs.%20Fares%20said%20this%20number%20does%20not%20include%20prisoners%20from%20Gaza%2C%20which%20he%20said%20Israel%20refuses%20to%20disclose.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20February%2C%20UN%20experts%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F02%2Fisrael-un-experts-alarmed-potential-reinstatement-death-penalty-terrorism%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpressed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20grave%20concern%20over%20the%20potential%20reinstatement%20of%20the%20death%20penalty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20laws%20%E2%80%9Csuffer%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20legal%20precision%2C%20infringe%20on%20critically%20important%20rights%2C%20and%20appear%20not%20to%20meet%20the%20required%20thresholds%20of%20legality%2C%20necessity%2C%20proportionality%2C%20and%20non-discrimination%20under%20international%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%20abolished%20the%20death%20penalty%20in%201954.%20The%20death%20penalty%20law%20has%20been%20proposed%20in%20Israel%20more%20than%20once%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20but%20so%20far%2C%20the%20Knesset%20has%20refused%20to%20legislate%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20order%20for%20the%20draft%20law%20to%20become%20effective%2C%20it%20will%20need%20to%20pass%20three%20readings%20in%20the%20Knesset.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPreceding%20the%20first%20reading%2C%20Gvir%20said%20the%20draft%20%E2%80%9Cis%20expected%20to%20receive%20support%20by%20all%20members%20of%20the%20Knesset.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700449439000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F11175255%2FScreenshot-2023-10-11-at-5.52.50-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-parliament-set-to-discuss-legalising-death-penalty-law-for-palestinian-prisoners%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20preliminary%20reading%20last%20March%2C%20the%20Knesset%20approved%20the%20draft%20law%20that%20would%20allow%20courts%20to%20impose%20the%20death%20penalty%20on%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20convicted%20of%20killing